		<td><b>Expansion cartridge</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As most NES cartridges have it's own CHRAM and maybe SRAM, wouldn't it be useful to have a expansion cartridge to only use one chram/SRAM chip? 
<br />SRAM could be bigger than 8kb and allow switching on cart for multiple savegames.
<br />Something like an Action Replay that adds that functions and makes carts that use it less expensive to reproduce.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

