	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />So in other words, you're asking for something like an <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aladdin_Deck_Enhancer" class="postlink">Aladdin Deck Enhancer</a>, except with SRAM support. There are several ways to engineer something like this in the modern era:
<br /><ul><li>UNROM-style behavior like the Camerica games, or something stronger with a cycle counter? </li><li>How much SRAM? </li><li>Is the SRAM battery-backed, or does it use serial flash instead to save on the cost of a battery circuit? </li><li>A separate boot ROM for save management, or a basic GUI to be linked into all games using this adapter? </li></ul>

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


