	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />A 32kB SRAM costs less than a $1.  Just putting a connector on an expansion board will cost more than that (and getting an enclosure for this stuff would cost far more, unless bare PCBs are what you had in mind).  And I think making it mapper-independent sorta defeats the usefulness of it, since then you still need a bunch of stuff on the game board, just like usual.  None of this will make stuff any cheaper.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


